---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@components/PageHero.astro';
import Button from '@components/Button.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Executive Director's Message"
  description="A message from CHRSD's Executive Director on the Foundation's mission, progress, and direction."
>
  <PageHero
    overline="About · Our identity"
    title="Executive Director's Message"
    lead="An annual reflection on where we stand, what we have learned, and where we are going."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container letter-wrap">

      <!-- SIDEBAR: Director card -->
      <aside class="director-card">
        <div class="director-avatar" aria-hidden="true">
          <span>MA</span>
        </div>
        <div class="director-info">
          <strong class="director-name">Mohammed Azizul Haque</strong>
          <span class="director-title">Executive Director</span>
          <span class="director-org">CHRSD Foundation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="director-links">
          <Button href="/about-us/team/" variant="outline">Meet the team</Button>
          <Button href="/get-involved/contact-us/" variant="ghost">Write to us</Button>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- LETTER -->
      <article class="letter prose">
        <p class="letter__date">June 2026</p>
        <p class="letter__salutation">Dear friends and partners,</p>

        <p>
          Fifty-four years ago, a small group of researchers and community organisers in
          Dhaka asked a simple question: <em>what would it take for the most marginalised
          people in Bangladesh to shape the policies that governed their own lives?</em>
          The Centre for Humanitarian Research and Social Development was founded on that
          question. It remains the animating force behind everything we do today.
        </p>

        <p>
          The world has changed dramatically since 1972. Bangladesh has made
          extraordinary strides — in poverty reduction, in women's empowerment, in
          climate adaptation, and in the digital transformation of public services.
          But the distance between policy intent and lived community experience remains
          as wide as ever in too many places. Filling that gap — with evidence, with
          advocacy, and with direct action — is still CHRSD's mandate.
        </p>

        <h3>A year of measurable progress</h3>

        <p>
          This year has been one of our most consequential. The National Smart
          Afforestation & Digital Monitoring Programme reached its first major milestone:
          over 8 crore saplings planted and digitally tracked across fourteen districts,
          with a verified survival rate of 71% — well above the national average. For
          each of those trees, there is a community member who planted it, a field
          technician who recorded its GPS coordinates, and a satellite image confirming
          it is still standing.
        </p>

        <p>
          The Smart Digital Attendance Management System is now operational in over
          12,000 government primary schools. Teacher accountability is improving,
          and — more importantly — children are learning in classrooms that are reliably
          staffed. The data tells a clear story; the families we have spoken to in the
          field tell an even clearer one.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our human rights team has provided free legal assistance to 340 individuals
          this year — people who could not otherwise have accessed a lawyer. Our
          socio-economic research division published three peer-reviewed studies on
          labour market informality and its relationship to extreme weather events.
          These are not numbers on a dashboard. They are people, households, and
          communities.
        </p>

        <h3>What we are learning</h3>

        <p>
          Scale without depth is a trap. We have been deliberate this year about
          asking not just <em>how many</em> but <em>how sustainably</em>. Are the trees
          we plant surviving because communities feel ownership over them — or because
          we are monitoring them? Are the schools we support improving because teachers
          are accountable to data — or because they feel respected and resourced?
          These are uncomfortable questions. We are building evaluation frameworks that
          force us to answer them honestly.
        </p>

        <p>
          We are also learning about the limits of technology. GIS and satellite
          monitoring are powerful tools — but they work only when layered onto deep
          community relationships. Data collected without trust is data collected badly.
          CHRSD's comparative advantage has always been that combination: rigorous
          methodology with genuine community embeddedness. We will not sacrifice the
          second for the first.
        </p>

        <h3>The road ahead</h3>

        <p>
          In the coming year we will launch Phase II of NSADMP, targeting an additional
          10 crore trees in coastal Bangladesh — a region facing acute climate stress.
          We will expand our legal aid programme into three new districts. And we will
          begin a multi-year evaluation of SDAMSMP to determine whether attendance
          improvements are translating into learning outcomes.
        </p>

        <p>
          None of this is possible without you — our volunteers, donors, partners, and
          the communities who open their doors to our field teams. Thank you for your
          trust. We do not take it lightly. We publish our audited accounts, our
          evaluation reports, and our programme data precisely because accountability
          to you is not a compliance exercise — it is the foundation of everything we do.
        </p>

        <p>
          There is always a way. We keep finding it, together.
        </p>

        <div class="letter__sign">
          <div class="signature" aria-hidden="true">Mohammed Azizul Haque</div>
          <div class="signature-block">
            <strong>Mohammed Azizul Haque</strong>
            <span>Executive Director, CHRSD Foundation</span>
            <span>Dhaka, June 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="letter__footer">
          <Button href="/impact/annual-reports/" variant="solid">Read the Annual Report</Button>
          <Button href="/about-us/team/" variant="outline">Meet the full team</Button>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .letter-wrap {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr;
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Director card */
  .director-card {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--color-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-green);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 32px 24px;
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .director-avatar {
    width: 88px; height: 88px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-forest); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  }
  .director-avatar span { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 30px; color: #fff; }
  .director-info { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
  .director-name { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 17px; color: var(--color-forest); }
  .director-title { font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-institutional); font-weight: 600; }
  .director-org { font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-slate); }
  .director-links { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; width: 100%; }
  .director-links .btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; }

  /* Letter / prose */
  .letter { max-width: 70ch; }
  .letter__date { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-slate); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .letter__salutation { font-size: 20px; font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-forest); margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .prose p { color: var(--color-slate); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-ink); }
  .prose h3 { font-size: 20px; color: var(--color-forest); margin: 36px 0 16px; padding-left: 16px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-gold); }

  /* Signature */
  .letter__sign { display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 24px; margin: 40px 0 36px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-green); }
  .signature {
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: 28px; color: var(--color-forest); font-style: italic;
    white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .signature-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px; }
  .signature-block strong { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; color: var(--color-forest); }
  .signature-block span { font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-slate); }

  .letter__footer { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .letter-wrap { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 36px; }
    .director-card { position: static; flex-direction: row; flex-wrap: wrap; text-align: left; }
    .director-links { flex-direction: row; }
    .director-links .btn { width: auto; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .letter__sign { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  }
</style>
